Only snap the cursor frame on large targets.

The bracket-snap read as "selection" on button-sized elements, which
felt like the cursor was taking over whatever you pointed at. Now the
frame only snaps to bounds when the element is at least 180x140 — big
enough that a camera-focus reticle reads as framing, not selecting.
Small interactives (buttons, chips, text links, inputs) keep the
cursor pointer-sized and simply tint the brackets acid, so the
pointer continues to point while still signalling interactivity. The
link-destination tag and press-pulse behave the same in both modes.

